  4→
  5→**Goal:** Replace direct Gmail OAuth in `nurge connect gmail` with Unipile hosted auth, and replace direct Gmail API sync with Convex-proxied Unipile email fetching — eliminating Google app verification requirements entirely.
  6→
  7→**Architecture:** CLI calls Convex HTTP endpoints to get a Unipile hosted auth link, opens it in browser, polls Convex for completion. Sync pulls emails from Convex (which fetches from Unipile) instead of hitting Gmail API directly. Direct Gmail API code (`internal/email/client.go`) is kept for now since `dispatcher.go` and `replies.go` still reference it — full removal is a separate task.
